Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
checkWhatIfTiming(25.10)                              checkWhatIfTiming(25.10)

Name
       checkWhatIfTiming  - Checks that at least one timing arc is defined for
       every port of a blackbox or blackblob

Syntax
        checkWhatIfTiming

       <blackBoxCellName>

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       Checks that at least one timing arc is defined  for  every  port  of  a
       blackbox or blackblob. You use this command to output the status of the
       timing  arcs for all ports to complete the blackbox or blackblob timing
       arc specifications for the remaining ports.

       You can use this command after the module definition of the blackbox or
       the blackblob is available with the I/O's in the Verilog netlist.

Parameters
       <blackBoxCellName>
              Specifies the name of the blackbox or blackblob cell.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the file to save the information.

Related Information
              * What-If Timing Analysis chapter in the Innovus User Guide

